 Mandriva Linux Security Advisory                         MDVSA-2008:182
 http://www.mandriva.com/security/
 _______________________________________________________________________

 Package : wordnet
 Date    : September 2, 2008
 Affected: 2008.0, 2008.1
 _______________________________________________________________________

 Problem Description:

 Rob Holland found several programming errors in WordNet which could
 lead to the execution or arbitrary code when used with untrusted input
 (CVE-2008-2149).
 
 The updated packages have been patched to prevent these issues.
 _______________________________________________________________________

 References:

 http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2008-2149
 _______________________________________________________________________

